Making a AIController Class
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Make a blueprint class -> AIController class
2. In the Event Graph, make a "AI MoveTo" action and link it with a "get Controlled Pawn" and "Get Player Character".
3. Make a "Set Timer by Function Name" and name the function
4. check the looping for loops and set the time for the time to repeat (seconds)
5. link it with "Event BeginPlay" 
6. make a "Custom Event" and name it as the name I set for the timer
7. compile and save
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Making a Pawn to control
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Make a blueprint class -> Pawn
2. add a Cube(or whatever Geometry I want) from "+Add Component"
3. change the settings (scale, color(Materials), etc.)
4. add a FloatingPawnMovement from "+Add Component"
5. Click the Pawn I made(self), and change the "AI Controller Class" to "EvilCubeAI(the AIController Class I made)"
6. compile and save
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Add A Nav Mesh Bounds
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Make a "Nav Mesh Bounds" from "Volumes"
2. compromise the size(scale) and location
3. check "Navigation" in "Show" to see the NavMeshBoundsVolume in green
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Destroying a Actor(Pawn) with a explosion
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. check the "Cube" from the Component section.
2. right click in the event graph and choose "Add event for Cube", "Collision", "Add on Component Hit"
3. make a "Spawn actor from Class" and choose a "Blueprint Effcet Explosion" and get the transform(location) from "Cube", "getworldtransform(get transform)"
4. make a "destroy component" from "Cube"
5. make a Sequence by Pressing "S" and left clicking
6. link Sequence 1 to spawnactor and 2 to destroy components
7. from "Return value" from spawnActor Blueprint Effect Explosion, drag it and "Promote to Variable" and name it as I want "Fire Explosion"
8. Click Fire Explosion and make a "On End Play" Event and make one on the end
9. link it with "Destroy Actor"
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


Spawning The AICube every second
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. make a "box trigger"
2. go to "Open Level Blueprints" and drag the "TriggerBox" into the Blueprint event
3. make a "Spawn AI from Class" and link the location with the TriggerBox by making a "Get Actor Location" in between
4. make a "Add Custom Event" and set a timer by "Set Timer by function name" and link it with The "BeginPlay Event"
5. name the function same as the "custom Event" and loop it with time.



Changing the speed for Cube
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. open "EvilCubePawn" and click on the FloatingPawnMovement
2. change the Max Speed, Acceleration, Deceleration, etc;.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
